Static global  :
Static variable has scope only in the file in which it is declared. 
It can't be accessed in any other file but its value remains intact 
if code is running in some other file means lifetime is in complete program .


Static local:
static local variable has scope in that function in which it is declared means 
it can't be used in other functions in the same file also, 
means scope is limited to the function in which it is declared while its life time is also through out the program. 
